This project studied torque-control behavior in a shunt DC motor through mathematical modeling and comparison of multiple control methods. The analysis focused on how electrical parameter changes influence torque-speed characteristics and operating regions.

The results highlighted the differences between several practical control approaches and provided engineering insight into controllability, efficiency, and performance trade-offs in DC motor operation.
result: Compared three DC-motor torque-control methods and evaluated their torque-speed performance trade-offs.
